{{Infobox Bilateral relations|Ecuador–Russia|Ecuador|Russia}}

'''Ecuador–Russia relations''' is the [[bilateralism|bilateral]] [[International relations|foreign relations]] between [[Ecuador]] and [[Russia]].  Ecuador has an embassy in Moscow, and Russia has an [[Embassy of Russia in Quito|embassy in Quito]].

Ecuador was one of the countries that offered [[Edward Snowden]] [[political asylum]] while he was in [[Moscow]]'s [[Sheremetyevo Airport]].

