{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}
[[File:Hulen 1.JPG|thumb]]
'''Hulen''' ('The Cave') is a student-driven rock club in [[Bergen]], Norway, that opened on 17 May 1969.<ref name="bt40">{{cite news|title=Bergtatt igjen|last=Fossen|first=Erik|date=26 September 2009|work=BTMagasinet|publisher=[[Bergens Tidende]]|pages=12–15|language=Norwegian}}</ref><ref name="ba40">{{cite news|url=http://www.ba.no/puls/article4540218.ece|title=Hulen fyller 40|last=Brøske|first=Bjørn Tore|date=26 August 2009|work=Bergensavisen|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2009-09-30|location=Bergen}}</ref> Hulen has its premises in an old bomb shelter below [[Nygårdshøyden]] in the city center of Bergen. The shelter is rented from the [[Norwegian Civil Defence]].<ref name="bt40"/> During its 40 years of existence Hulen has been threatened with bankruptcy etc., but has managed to continue because of their volunteers and supporters.<ref name="bt40"/>

==History==
Hulen was once an air-raid shelter, which in 1968 was converted into a club for local students in Bergen, and opened on 17 May 1969.<ref name="HulenHomePage">.[http://hulen.no/Historikk/ History section at Hulen's homepage](in Norwegian)</ref> The reason was partly that the students' old resident, Parkveien 1, was torn down.<ref name="HulenHomePage"/> In over 42 years that have elapsed since that time Hulen has also always served as a cultural alternative for students and music people.<ref name="HulenHomePage"/> Hulen is driven by pure idealism.<ref name="HulenHomePage"/> Around 80 people sacrifice some of their best years to keep the wheels rolling in the cave.<ref name="HulenHomePage"/>

