{{Infobox mountain | name = Les Diablons | photo = Les Diablons - Depuis Sorebois.jpg | photo_caption = View of Les Diablons from above [[Zinal]] | elevation_m = 3609 | elevation_ref = | prominence_m = 379 | prominence_ref = <ref>Retrieved from the [[Swisstopo]] topographic maps and [[Google Earth]]. The key col is the Col de Tracuit (3,230 m).</ref> | parent_peak = | location = [[Valais]], [[Switzerland]] | map = Switzerland | map_caption = Location in Switzerland | range = [[Pennine Alps]] | coordinates = {{coord|46|8|32.8|N|7|40|15.7|E|type:mountain_region:CH_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | range_coordinates = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
'''Les Diablons''' are a [[mountain]] of the Swiss [[Pennine Alps]], overlooking [[Zinal]] in the canton of [[Valais]]. They lie between the valleys of [[Anniviers]] and [[Turtmanntal|Turtmann]] on the subrange of the Pennine Alps that culminates at the [[Weisshorn]].
South of Les Diablons, on the Tracuit pass, is located the [[Tracuit Hut]].
==See also== *[[List of mountains of Switzerland]]
