'''National Union for Democracy''' ({{lang-pt|União Nacional para a Democracia}}) is a [[political party]] in [[Angola]]. The party was founded on October 2, 1991.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cne.ao/partidos.cfm|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080628223431/http://www.cne.ao/partidos.cfm|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2008-06-28|title=Comissão Nacional Eleitoral de Angola|website=www.cne.ao|access-date=2017-07-06}}</ref> The party is a member of the coalition [[New Democracy (Angola)|New Democracy]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Amundsen|first=Inge|last2=Weimer|first2=Markus|date=2008|title=Opposition Parties and the 2008 Parliamentary Elections in Angola|url=http://www.cmi.no/publications/file/?3103=opposition-parties-and-the-upcoming-2008|journal=CMI Working Paper|language=en|volume=WP 2008:9}}</ref> The party was previously a member of the coalition [[Parties of the Civilian Opposition]], but pulled out of it and took part in founding New Democracy in December 2006.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.angoladicas.com/notices_detail.asp?ID=8593&a=1&lang=pt |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-08-31 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707143417/http://www.angoladicas.com/notices_detail.asp?ID=8593&a=1&lang=pt |archivedate=2011-07-07 |df= }}</ref>

