{{Infobox airport | name = Poprad–Tatry Airport | nativename = <small>''Letisko Poprad-Tatry''</small> | nativename-a = | nativename-r = | image = Terminál letiska Poprad-Tatry.jpg | image-width = 250 | IATA = TAT | ICAO = LZTT | pushpin_map = Slovakia | pushpin_map_caption = Location of airport in Slovakia | pushpin_label = TAT | pushpin_label_position = right | type = Public | owner = | operator = | city-served = [[Poprad]], [[Slovakia]] | location = <!--If different than above--> | elevation-f = 2,356 | elevation-m = 718 | coordinates = {{Coord|49|04|25|N|20|14|28|E|type:airport}} | website = [http://www.airport-poprad.sk/ airport-poprad.sk] | metric-elev = | metric-rwy = | r1-number = 09/27 | r1-length-f = 8,530 | r1-length-m = 2,600 | r1-surface = [[Concrete]] | r2-number = 07R/25L | r2-length-f = 2,493 | r2-length-m = 760 | r2-surface = [[Grass]] | r3-number = 07L/25R | r3-length-f = 2,493 | r3-length-m = 760 | r3-surface = [[Grass]] | stat-year = | stat1-header = | stat1-data = | stat2-header = | stat2-data = | footnotes = }}
'''Poprad–Tatry Airport''' ({{lang-sk|Letisko Poprad-Tatry}}) {{airport codes|TAT|LZTT}}, is an airport in the [[Slovakia|Slovak]] ski resort town of [[Poprad]]. It is an airport with one of the highest elevations in Central Europe, at 718 m, which is 150 m higher than [[Innsbruck Airport]] in [[Austria]], and 989 m lower than [[Samedan Airport]] in [[Switzerland]].
== Airlines and destinations == The airport serves schedule and charter airline operations, is a base for [[MEDEVAC|search and rescue]] air services, and handles [[general aviation]]. It does not offer any domestic flights. Charter flights are mainly operated in winter. Medical flights, VIP flights, ''ad hoc'' charters and ACMI flight also operate from the airport.
The following airlines serve scheduled services to and from Poprad–Tatry Airport: {{airport-dest-list <!-- --> | [[airBaltic]] | '''Seasonal:''' [[Riga International Airport|Riga]] <!-- --> | [[SkyUp]] | '''Seasonal:''' [[Kyiv International Airport (Zhuliany)|Kiev–Zhuliany]] (begins 29 December 2018)<ref>https://skyup.aero/uk/</ref> <!-- --> | [[Wizz Air]] | [[London Luton|London–Luton]] <!-- --> }}
